==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hebetate
<hw>Heb"e*tate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Hebetated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Hebetating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>hebetatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>hebetare</ets> to dull. See
<er>Hebete</er>.]</ety> <def>To render obtuse; to dull; to blunt; to
stupefy; <as>as, to <ex>hebetate</ex> the intellectual
faculties</as>.</def> <rj><au>Southey</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hebetate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hebetate
<hw>Heb"e*tate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Obtuse;
dull.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having a dull or blunt and soft
point.</def> <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hebetation</ent>⟦br⟧
